    <prj:ScienceGoal mode="Other">
        <prj:name>Determining the magnetic field properties within TW Hya</prj:name>
        <prj:note>We intend to observe the magnetic field strength and structure in the protoplanetary disk TW Hya spatially resolved. We will trace these magnetic field properties with a sensitivity for 0.3% polarization at a 3 sigma level, resolved on 0.19". In doing so, we will constrain for the first time the magnetic field properties within a protoplanetary disk. The gained knowlegde about these properties will then be used to clarify the theoretically suggested influence of magnetic fields on the evolution of protoplanetary disks for the first time.
Since spectral line polarization is not offered in Cycle 3, we will not observe any spectroscopic data.</prj:note>
