        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>As required for the full polarization mode, we consider a band width of 7.5 GHz with a minimum of atmospheric absorption lines within the selected wavelength range. All four spectral windows shall operate in the TDM mode.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We want to reveal the magnetic field strength and structure of this nearly face-on protoplanetary disk, TW Hya by measuring the polarization degree
and polarization angle across the disk. Because of the angular momentum, it is expected to find a toroidal magnetic field structure in the disk. The polarization pattern cancels out if symmetric, as is usually the case on large scales. Thus, the better the spatial resolution the less cancellation of the observed polarization structure occures. At the same time, we are sensitivity limited by an expected minimum polarization degree of 0.3%. We find the optimal combination of sensitivity, spatial resolution, and observing time with a resolution of 0.19". With this, we will observe 22 polarization vectors
across TW Hya, and determine the magnetic field properties, its strength and structure, for the first time.
We set the requested largest angular scale to the maximal possible with this single ALMA configuration to resolve the disk on the known extent
at 230GHz (1.06" x 1.04"; Isella+ 2009). Additionally, we will probe the total dust emission at 2x larger radii by using the high sensitivity of ALMA
- without the need of any additional observation time.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We propose for full polarization observations of the protoplanetary disk TW Hya with ALMA in band 6. The total flux of TW Hya at 230GHz is 543mJy
(Isella+ 2009), distributed over an disk extent of 1.06" x 1.04" (Isella+ 2009). We expect a minimum polarization degree of 0.3% which we want to trace
with a sufficiently high signal-to-noise ratio, i.e., S/N=3 at a spatial resolution of 0.19". Resulting from these specifications, the needed RMS is 9.46uJy. </prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
